Yesterday, the National Securities Market Commission (CNMV) allowed the exclusion, which Inversora Mer participates in, against Federico Paternin on October 9.
The Supervisory Authority explained that it authorises this operation as it understands that its conditions are in line with the applicable standards and considers that the content of the explanatory brochures submitted following the 2 December amendments is "sufficient".
CNMV specified that the offer is aimed at acquiring 550,008 shares of Federico Paternin’s stock at a price of 7.65 euros per share, representing 8.95% of the company’s capital, which consists of 6,142,786 shares admitted to trading on the Madrid and Bilbao stock exchanges.
He further explained that 5,592,778 million shares had been immobilised which could not be transferred in any way until the offer specified that the price had been fixed by Federico Paternin in accordance with the provisions of the applicable standards had been concluded.
New tools for valuing cars
In these days of storms and accidents earn not only car repair shops.
Each day, thousands of cars that have suffered an insurance claim are towed to a repair shop where an expert must estimate the damage and repair costs.
No insurance event is the same, and calculating the cost of parts and labor time can be a long and complex job.
Calculate repair costs manually from 20,000 to 30,000 euros including parts and labor can take two or three hours.
However, with the support of new computer tools, it would be a matter of minutes
Therefore, almost 100% of experts use this type of system.
Service providers and insurance and maintenance forecasting solutions are dedicated to gathering information from manufacturers to then develop and offer their customers a useful tool.
In Spain, Audatex, from the American group Solera, is a leading company; 80% of the evaluations are carried out with its products.
Other companies that compete in the field of valuation tools and the development of information about the sector are GtMotive and Eurotax.
Working with the data provided by manufacturers is not at all easy.
According to Eduardo Velázquez, Sales Director of Audatex, 63 manufacturers and importers work in Spain and each of them provides them with information in a different format.
In addition, the amount of data to be processed is still growing, as more versions, variants and engine solutions have been introduced in the last five years than in the previous fifteen years.
Once a new vehicle enters the market, these businesses will start operating.
This is a very hot job, because it is necessary to catalog each of the thousands of parts of the vehicle and set its price.
In addition, for each model, "intelligent" graphic processing is carried out, where it is possible to "punch out" individual parts of tourist cars.
As for the model with massive sales, the work can be done in a week, if the process is very fast.
As for the minority car, it can take three or four months. At present, Audatex has complete information on 99.2% of cars sold in Spain.
Among the most exclusive models they have information about are Porsche, but not Ferrari or Lamborghini, for example.
In terms of mobile park in circulation, they exceed 99%.
To carry out the work of documenting and developing databases, Audatex has eight centers divided around the world (Spain, France, Germany, USA, Brazil, Mexico, China and Japan) and each of them specializes in specific brands.
The national seat is in Alcobendas (Madrid).
There, more than a hundred technicians (normally mechanical experts) work simultaneously with three computer screens.
